2016–17 PlusLiga

2016–17 PlusLiga was the 81st season of Polish Championship (17th season as professional league - PlusLiga) organized by Professional Volleyball League SA () under the supervision of Polish Volleyball Federation ().

The number of teams competing this season increased from 14 the past season to 16. GKS Katowice and Espadon Szczecin were the two teams added to the league.

In season 2016/2017 Poland was represented by Asseco Resovia Rzeszów and ZAKSA Kędzierzyn-Koźle in CEV Champions League, also PGE Skra Bełchatów gained a place in this tournament because of CEV Champions League qualification.

ZAKSA Kędzierzyn-Koźle achieved 7th title of Polish Champion.

